{"metadata":{"kernelspec":{"language":"python","display_name":"Python 3","name":"python3"},"language_info":{"name":"python","version":"3.12.12","mimetype":"text/x-python","codemirror_mode":{"name":"ipython","version":3},"pygments_lexer":"ipython3","nbconvert_exporter":"python","file_extension":".py"},"kaggle":{"accelerator":"none","dataSources":[{"sourceType":"datasetVersion","sourceId":15468030,"datasetId":9895711,"databundleVersionId":16390841}],"dockerImageVersionId":31328,"isInternetEnabled":true,"language":"python","sourceType":"notebook","isGpuEnabled":false}},"nbformat_minor":4,"nbformat":4,"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"RQ1 – Regional and temporal sales & profit patterns","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# RQ1: Regional and temporal sales & profit patterns\n\nimport pandas as pd\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt\nimport seaborn as sns\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\n# -------------------\n# 1. Load data\n# -------------------\nDATA_PATH = Path(\"/kaggle/input/datasets/bibirehana/global-e-commarce-sales-data-analysis/global_ecommerce_sales.csv\")\ndf = pd.read_csv(DATA_PATH)\n\n# -------------------\n# 2. Parse dates & create YearMonth\n# -------------------\ndf['Order_Date'] = pd.to_datetime(df['Order_Date'])\ndf['YearMonth'] = df['Order_Date'].dt.to_period('M').astype(str)\n\n# -------------------\n# 3. Aggregate by Region and YearMonth\n# -------------------\nagg_rq1 = (\n    df.groupby(['Region', 'YearMonth'], as_index=False)\n      .agg(\n          Total_Sales=('Total_Sales', 'sum'),\n          Total_Profit=('Profit', 'sum')\n      )\n)\n\n# -------------------\n# 4. Save table as CSV\n# -------------------\nOUTPUT_DIR = Path(\"./rq1_outputs\")\nOUTPUT_DIR.mkdir(exist_ok=True, parents=True)\n\nagg_rq1.to_csv(OUTPUT_DIR / \"RQ1_Table_Monthly_Region_Sales_Profit.csv\", index=False)\n\n# -------------------\n# 5. Plot figure\n# -------------------\nsns.set(style=\"whitegrid\")\n\nplt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\nsns.lineplot(\n    data=agg_rq1,\n    x='YearMonth',\n    y='Total_Sales',\n    hue='Region',\n    marker='o'\n)\nplt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')\nplt.title(\"Monthly Total Sales by Region\")\nplt.xlabel(\"Year-Month\")\nplt.ylabel(\"Total Sales\")\nplt.tight_layout()\n\n# -------------------\n# 6. Save figure as PDF and show the figures.\n# -------------------\nplt.savefig(OUTPUT_DIR / \"RQ1_Figure1_Regional_Monthly_Sales.pdf\", format=\"pdf\")\nplt.show()\nplt.close()","metadata":{"_uuid":"8f2839f25d086af736a60e9eeb907d3b93b6e0e5","_cell_guid":"b1076dfc-b9ad-4769-8c92-a6c4dae69d19","trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-05-04T16:06:48.675764Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-05-04T16:06:48.676102Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-05-04T16:06:50.765420Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-05-04T16:06:48.676072Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-05-04T16:06:50.764400Z"}},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 1000x600 with 1 Axes>","image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":6},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### Interpretation of chart.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"- Asia Pacific and Europe lead overall sales, consistently showing the highest monthly totals.\n\n- North America maintains mid‑level, stable sales, below the top two regions but above the rest.\n\n- South America and Middle East & Africa show the lowest sales, indicating smaller or emerging markets.\n\n- Sales patterns appear stable, with no extreme spikes or collapses across any region.\n\n- Seasonal or cyclical trends may be present, as the lines show periodic rises and dips over months.\n\n- Asia Pacific shows the strongest upward momentum, suggesting growing demand in that region.\n\n- Regional disparities are clear, with top regions generating several times the sales of lower‑performing ones.- ","metadata":{}}]}
